{"node_id": "4f6d83cdfa00568995b638a6929707ef", "title": "Definite integrals: common functions", "description": "Evaluate definite integrals with a variety of functions including rational, square root, cube root, exponential, and natural logs.", "topic_path": ["Khan Academy (English - US curriculum)", "Math", "AP®︎ Calculus AB", "Integration and accumulation of change", "Finding antiderivatives and integrals: basic rules and notation: definite integrals", "Definite integrals: common functions"], "assessment_items": [{"item_id": "e4ac4e9cdbbf56fbb14270e847416e55", "question_content": "**Evaluate the definite integral.**\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^2_{1}\\left(\\dfrac{12}{x^2}-1\\right)\\,dx = $ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["First, use the power rule:\n\n$\\begin{align}\\displaystyle\\int^2_{1}\\left(\\dfrac{12}{x^2}-1\\right)\\,dx~&=\\displaystyle\\int^2_{1}\\left(12x^{-2}-1\\right)\\,dx\n\\\\&=~(-12x^{-1}-x)\\Bigg|^\\blueD2_{\\maroonD1}\\end{align}$", "Second, plug in the limits of integration:\n\n$[-12\\cdot\\blueD2^{-1}-\\blueD2]-[-12\\cdot\\maroonD1^{-1}-\\maroonD1] = -8+13 = 5$.", "The answer:\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^2_{1}\\left(\\dfrac{12}{x^2}-1\\right)\\,dx = 5$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 5}]}}}, {"item_id": "e6ca521ec2d45609b09745e86a1a4353", "question_content": "**Evaluate the definite integral.**\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{-2}_{-1}\\left(\\dfrac{16-x^3}{x^3}\\right)\\,dx = $ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["First, use the power rule:\n\n$\\begin{align}\\displaystyle\\int^{-2}_{-1}\\left(\\dfrac{16-x^3}{x^3}\\right)\\,dx~&=~\\displaystyle\\int^{-2}_{-1}\\left(\\dfrac{16}{x^3}-\\dfrac{x^3}{x^3}\\right)\\,dx\n\\\\&=~\\displaystyle\\int^{-2}_{-1}\\left(16{x^{-3}}-{1}\\right)\\,dx\n\\\\&=(-8x^{-2}-x)\\Bigg|^\\blueD{-2}_{\\maroonD{-1}}\\end{align}$", "Second, plug in the limits of integration:\n\n$[-8\\cdot(\\blueD{-2})^{-2}-(\\blueD{-2})]-[-8\\cdot(\\maroonD{-1})^{-2}-(\\maroonD{-1})] = 0+7 = 7$.", "The answer:\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{-2}_{-1}\\left(\\dfrac{16-x^3}{x^3}\\right)\\,dx= 7$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 7}]}}}, {"item_id": "776b5cff12bd5080a30b0e3b90e86ffe", "question_content": "**Evaluate the definite integral.**\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{-3}_{-1}\\left(\\dfrac{27}{x^4}-3\\right)\\,dx = $ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["First, use the power rule:\n\n$\\begin{align}\\displaystyle\\int^{-3}_{-1}\\left(\\dfrac{27}{x^4}-3\\right)\\,dx~&=~\\displaystyle\\int^{-3}_{-1}\\left({27}{x^{-4}}-3\\right)\\,dx\n\\\\&=(-9x^{-3}-3x)\\Bigg|^\\blueD{-3}_{\\maroonD{-1}}\\end{align}$", "Second, plug in the limits of integration:\n\n$[-9\\cdot(\\blueD{-3})^{-3}-3(\\blueD{-3})]-[-9\\cdot(\\maroonD{-1})^{-3}-3\\cdot(\\maroonD{-1})] = \\dfrac{28}{3}-12 = -\\dfrac{8}{3}$.", "The answer:\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{-3}_{-1}\\left(\\dfrac{27}{x^4}-3\\right)\\,dx = -\\dfrac{8}{3}$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"answerForms": ["proper", "improper"], "maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": -2.6666666666666665}]}}}, {"item_id": "4696dd6152d2545abfe184e787be8128", "question_content": "**Evaluate the definite integral.**\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^4_{3}\\left(4+\\dfrac{24}{x^2}\\right)\\,dx = $ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["First, use the power rule:\n\n$\\begin{align}\\displaystyle\\int^4_{3}\\left(4+\\dfrac{24}{x^2}\\right)\\,dx~&= \\displaystyle\\int^4_{3}\\left(4+24x^{-2}\\right)\\,dx\n\\\\&=\n~(4x-24x^{-1})\\Bigg|^\\blueD4_{\\maroonD3}\\end{align}$", "Second, plug in the limits of integration:\n\n$[4\\cdot\\blueD4-24\\cdot\\blueD4^{-1}]-[4\\cdot\\maroonD3-24\\cdot\\maroonD3^{-1}] = 10-4 = 6$.", "The answer:\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^4_{3}\\left(4+\\dfrac{24}{x^2}\\right)\\,dx = 6$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 6}]}}}, {"item_id": "588c718871ea585c996f16094a31aded", "question_content": "**Evaluate the definite integral.**\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{-1}_{-5}\\left(\\dfrac{x^6-25x^4}{x^6}\\right)\\,dx = $ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["First, use the power rule:\n\n$\\begin{align}\\displaystyle\\int^{-1}_{-5}\\left(\\dfrac{x^6-25x^4}{x^6}\\right)\\,dx~&=~\\displaystyle\\int^{-1}_{-5}\\left(\\dfrac{x^6}{x^6}-\\dfrac{25x^4}{x^6}\\right)\\,dx\n\\\\&=~\\displaystyle\\int^{-1}_{-5}\\left(1-25x^{-2}\\right)\\,dx\n\\\\&=(x+25x^{-1})\\Bigg|^\\blueD{-1}_{\\maroonD{-5}}\\end{align}$", "Second, plug in the limits of integration:\n\n$[\\blueD{-1}+25\\cdot(\\blueD{-1})^{-1}]-[\\maroonD{-5}+25\\cdot(\\maroonD{-5})^{-1}] = -26+10 = -16$.", "The answer:\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{-1}_{-5}\\left(\\dfrac{x^6-25x^4}{x^6}\\right)\\,dx= -16$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": -16}]}}}, {"item_id": "03f696a9e7045e948671b66d257b866a", "question_content": "**Evaluate the definite integral.**\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{16}_{4}\\left(3\\sqrt{x}\\right)\\,dx = $ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["First, use the power rule:\n\n$\\begin{align}\\displaystyle\\int^{16}_{4}\\left(3\\sqrt{x}\\right)\\,dx ~&=~\\displaystyle\\int^{16}_{4}\\left(3x^{\\frac12}\\right)\\,dx\n\\\\&=(2x^\\frac32)\\Bigg|^\\blueD{16}_{\\maroonD4}\\end{align}$", "Second, plug in the limits of integration:\n\n$(2\\cdot\\blueD{16}^{\\frac32})-(2\\cdot\\maroonD4^{\\frac32}) = 128-16 = 112$.", "The answer:\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{16}_{4}\\left(3\\sqrt{x}\\right)\\,dx ~=~112$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": 112}]}}}, {"item_id": "ca28017038d65cdca127b2610cdede1d", "question_content": "**Evaluate the definite integral.**\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{25}_{0}\\left(-6\\sqrt{x}\\right)\\,dx = $ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["First, use the power rule:\n\n$\\begin{align}\\displaystyle\\int^{25}_{0}\\left(-6\\sqrt{x}\\right)\\,dx ~&=~\\displaystyle\\int^{25}_{0}\\left(-6x^{\\frac12}\\right)\\,dx\n\\\\&=(-4x^\\frac32)\\Bigg|^\\blueD{25}_{\\maroonD0}\\end{align}$", "Second, plug in the limits of integration:\n\n$(-4\\cdot\\blueD{25}^{\\frac32})-(-4\\cdot\\maroonD0^{\\frac32}) = -500+0 = -500$.", "The answer:\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{25}_{0}\\left(-6\\sqrt{x}\\right)\\,dx ~=~-500$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError": null, "message": "", "simplify": "required", "status": "correct", "strict": false, "value": -500}]}}}, {"item_id": "ce6d4f03a2185e0eaf6a32e3dbd3e4dd", "question_content": "**Evaluate the definite integral.**\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{1}_{9}\\left(-15\\sqrt{x}\\right)\\,dx = $ [[☃ numeric-input 1]]", "hints": ["First, use the power rule:\n\n$\\begin{align}\\displaystyle\\int^{1}_{9}\\left(-15\\sqrt{x}\\right)\\,dx ~&=~\\displaystyle\\int^{1}_{9}\\left(-15x^{\\frac12}\\right)\\,dx\n\\\\&=(-10x^\\frac32)\\Bigg|^\\blueD{1}_{\\maroonD{9}}\\end{align}$", "Second, plug in the limits of integration:\n\n$(-10\\cdot\\blueD{1}^{\\frac32})-(-10\\cdot\\maroonD{9}^{\\frac32}) = -10+270 = 260$.", "The answer:\n\n$\\displaystyle\\int^{1}_{9}\\left(-15\\sqrt{x}\\right)\\,dx ~=~260$"], "widget_types": ["numeric-input"], "answer_data": {"numeric-input 1": {"type": "numeric-input", "answers": [{"maxError